CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1951, pg. 22 reads: "I Do Solemnly Swear" - These Alpha men strike a jovial note as they pose for the cameraman after installation ceremonies held in Alpha House, 3046 Centre Avenue, recently. Shown, left to right, are Atty. A.D. Stevenson, who swore in the new officers; Alexander Allen, master of ceremonies, and the men taking oaths: George Mason, sergeant-at-arms; H.D. McCullough, financial secretary and associate editor of the Sphinx; Dr. R. W. Taylor, treasurer; Atty. Wilbur C. Douglass, secretary; Dr. Charles R. Cephas of New Brighton, vice president, and Charles H. Cuthbert, president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman wearing dark hat with wide brim, standing with Dr. R. W. Taylor, standing in doorway of Alpha Phi Alpha house during installation ceremonies, 3046 Centre Avenue
